@startuml Sequence Diagram - Job Application
!theme plain

title Sequence Diagram: Matching & Application Tracking

actor Student
participant "Frontend Client" as UI
participant "Backend Gateway" as API
participant "Evaluation & Matching" as EM
participant "Communication & Tracking" as CT
participant "AI Agent" as AI
database "MongoDB" as DB
actor Recruiter

== 1. Profile Matching & Recommendation ==
Student -> UI: Logs into platform
UI -> API: GET /api/recommendations/jobs
API -> EM: Request best matches for Student ID

EM -> DB: Fetch Student Skills & Preferences
DB --> EM: User Profile Data
EM -> DB: Fetch Active Job Postings
DB --> EM: Job Postings List

EM -> AI: Compute match scores (Profile vs Jobs)
AI --> EM: Ranked Recommendations & Reasons
EM --> API: Return top matches
API --> UI: Render Job Feed

== 2. Application & Tracking ==
Student -> UI: Clicks "Apply" to a match
UI -> API: POST /api/applications/apply
API -> CT: Initialize application timeline

CT -> DB: Create Application Record (Status: Applied)
CT -> Recruiter: Send Notification (New Candidate)
CT --> API: Success Response
API --> UI: Show Applcation Confirmation

== 3. Recruiter Review ==
Recruiter -> UI: Reviews matched candidate list
UI -> API: GET /api/applications/candidates
API -> DB: Fetch candidate profiles
DB --> API: Return candidates
API --> UI: Display to Recruiter

Recruiter -> UI: Moves candidate to "Interview"
UI -> API: PUT /api/applications/status
API -> CT: Update tracking timeline
CT -> DB: Save new status
CT -> Student: Send Interview Notification
@enduml
